Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.15,0:00:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs130\bord0\pos(950,950)\b0\fsp0.4}地         球         脉         动 {\fsp0.5}  I I
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.85,0:00:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,世界上超过八千米的山峰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are only fourteen peaks in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.06,0:00:44.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,屈指可数\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that rise to over 8000 metres.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.61,0:00:57.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们全部位于喜马拉雅地区\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}All of them are here, in the Himalayas.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.86,0:01:11.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在极端低温与暴风雪的洗礼下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Lethally cold, scoured by gales and blizzards,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.79,0:01:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些山脉成为地球上生存条件最苛刻的地区\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}these mountains are among the most hostile places on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.26,0:01:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而  仍有动物能够生活在这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Yet, a few special animals manage to live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.17,0:01:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雪豹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Snow leopards.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.13,0:01:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,与所有高山生物相同\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Like all creatures of the high mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.71,0:01:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了生存  他们必须从体型和行为上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they have had to adapt both their body and their behaviour
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.51,0:01:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,充分适应环境\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}in order to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.41,0:02:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,极高海拔之上的生存\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Life at extreme altitude
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.93,0:02:05.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塑造出了这个星球上最顽强的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}has shaped some of the toughest animals on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.10,0:02:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000,1000)\fs120\bord0\b0\pos(960,1300)}山        脉
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.41,0:02:32.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿拉伯半岛上的山地被阳光炙烤得发烫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The sunbaked mountains of the Arabian Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.40,0:02:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs60\fsp5\fad(1000,1000)\pos(960,1100)\bord0\b0}画 外 音\N{\fs90}大卫 · 爱登堡   爵士
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.61,0:02:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们的海拔也许只是喜马拉雅山脉的零头\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They may only be a fraction of the height of the Himalayas,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.40,0:02:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但却异常险峻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but they are still so dizzyingly steep
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.70,0:02:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很多地方几乎无法立足\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that in many places it's almost impossible to get a foothold.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.91,0:03:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而努比亚羱羊还是栖息于此\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Yet Nubian ibex have made this their home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.52,0:03:18.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,羱羊选择在最陡峭的绝壁上养育幼仔\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The ibex choose the steepest cliffs to raise their young,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.32,0:03:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,环境安全  没有天敌\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}in safety, beyond the reach of predators.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.39,0:03:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在生活在这里也要付出代价\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But living in this sanctuary comes with a cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.51,0:03:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,山崖过于陡峭\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These nursery slopes are so steep,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.75,0:03:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几乎没有任何积水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}there is almost no standing water up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.65,0:04:01.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了饮水  羱羊必须下到\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So to drink, an ibex family must descend into the valley...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.77,0:04:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,三百米下的峡谷之中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}...1,000 feet below.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.50,0:04:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,母羊选出一条最安全的下山路径\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The mothers pick out the safest way down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.77,0:04:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,四只柔软的分趾蹄胜过最好用的登山鞋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With soft cloven hooves that grip better than any climbing shoe,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.15,0:04:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让他们成为最高超的登山者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they are the most accomplished mountaineers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.31,0:04:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但新生的雏羊还在蹒跚学步\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the newborn kids are still having to find their feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.69,0:04:47.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是他们第一次下山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is their first descent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.29,0:04:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一次失蹄就可能一命呜呼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}One mistake could make it their last.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.10,0:05:16.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟着成年羱羊  小羊们终于到达山谷\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Following the adults, the kids finally reach the valley.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.09,0:05:24.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但回到平地上  他们就很容易遭到攻击\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But once on level ground, they're vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.69,0:05:35.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赤狐埋伏许久了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Red foxes lie in wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.45,0:05:51.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一有危险迹象\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At the first sign of danger,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.96,0:05:55.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,羱羊幼仔便本能地奔回陡坡\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the young ibex instinctively run back to steeper ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.20,0:06:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但爬上这块突出的岩石可能是个错误\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But heading for this particular rocky outcrop could be a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.05,0:06:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这有九米高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a 30-foot drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.90,0:06:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赤狐把它们困住了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The fox has them trapped...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.97,0:06:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或者看起来是这样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}or so it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.06,0:06:47.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这正是羱羊与生俱来的本领\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is what ibex were born to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.88,0:07:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,四散而逃的羊群让赤狐难以选择目标\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Scattering makes it hard for the fox to pick a target.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.11,0:07:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,显然它也无法追上峭壁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And it certainly can't follow them up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.00,0:07:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只能等待某只羱羊失蹄跌落\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}All it can do is wait for one to slip and fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.87,0:07:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这些小羊学得很快\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But these youngsters are fast learners,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.38,0:07:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在几乎可以和双亲一样如履平地了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they're now almost as sure-footed as their parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.25,0:08:38.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赤狐只能去别处觅食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The fox will have to find its meal elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.17,0:08:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天还真不是个好日子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's just not been a good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.41,0:09:00.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小羱羊终于喝上水了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now, at last, the young ibex can drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.56,0:09:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但很快他们又得\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But they'll soon need to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.64,0:09:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回到峭壁上的安全区域\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}return to the safety of the sheer cliffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.59,0:09:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在峭壁上行走固然很难\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Mastering precipitous terrain is always challenging,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.01,0:09:20.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但对于高山动物而言\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but there are more fundamental problems
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.13,0:09:21.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有更根本的难题\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for life in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.87,0:09:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿尔卑斯山脉  欧洲最高的山峰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Alps. Europe's highest peaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.43,0:09:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,时至冬季  食物极度匮乏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's winter, and food is desperately short.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.89,0:10:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,金雕不得不花费整个白天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A golden eagle has to spend every daylight hour
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.16,0:10:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,俯视山坡  寻找食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}scanning the slopes for something, somewhere, to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.98,0:10:23.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,长达两米的翼展让她\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Her seven-foot wingspan allows her to glide effortlessly
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.90,0:10:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一天可以轻松滑翔一百六十公里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for 100 miles in a single day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.55,0:10:38.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非凡的视力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Her extraordinary eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.31,0:10:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让她可以看到三公里外的猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}enable her to spot prey from two miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.33,0:10:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但她并非这里唯一的觅食者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But she is not the only one who's looking for food.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.75,0:11:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一旦发现良机  必须快速行动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}When she spots a chance, she must move fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.14,0:11:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她能以三百二十公里的时速俯冲而下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She can dive at 200 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.16,0:11:10.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有游隼能飞得更快\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Only a peregrine is faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.73,0:11:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在冬季  即使鹰类也几乎完全仰赖腐尸度日\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}During winter, even eagles rely almost entirely on carrion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.49,0:11:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是一只死去的狐狸\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a dead fox,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.30,0:11:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这顿美餐能让她支撑数日\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and it could sustain her for days.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.38,0:12:01.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其它食腐者只能等着了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Other scavengers must defer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.93,0:12:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,饥饿的乌鸦很快重新鼓起勇气\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The hungry crows soon regain their courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.32,0:12:13.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们想尽办法  试图分一杯羹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They'll try any trick to steal a morsel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.51,0:12:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,顽固地令人厌烦\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And they are annoyingly persistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.92,0:12:50.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这群乌鸦是她最不需要担心的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But this mob are the least of her worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.43,0:13:01.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只更大的金雕抢走了食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A bigger eagle takes control.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.24,0:13:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这顿美餐太过重要  不能轻易放弃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But this kill is too important to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.77,0:13:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,必须奋起一搏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So she must fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.13,0:13:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她暂时抢回了尸体\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For the moment, she's won the carcass back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.51,0:13:37.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这样的猎物会引来方圆数公里内所有的鹰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But a kill like this will attract every eagle for miles around.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.59,0:14:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最终依然是最强者赢得大部分食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As ever, the strongest wins the lion's share.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.65,0:14:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抢不到那具尸体\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Unable to defend the carcass any longer,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.34,0:14:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第一只雕只能继续它的觅食之旅\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the first eagle must now continue its search.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.30,0:14:24.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许下一次饱餐就是数日之后的事情了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It may be many days before she feeds again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.61,0:14:31.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有最具竞争力的生物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Only the most competitive
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.50,0:14:34.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,才能在山脉的寒冬中存活下来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}will survive the perils of the mountain winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.62,0:15:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一场雪崩\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}An avalanche.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.22,0:15:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,十万吨积雪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}100,000 tonnes of snow
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.01,0:15:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以一百三十公里的时速席卷而下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}travelling at 80 miles an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.16,0:15:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,足以粉碎沿途的一切\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}capable of smashing everything in its path.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.62,0:15:56.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,北美洲的山脉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The mountains of North America
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.62,0:16:00.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每年要发生数千起雪崩\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are hit by thousands of avalanches every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.16,0:16:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而有一种动物整个冬季\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Yet one animal spends the whole winter slumbering
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.48,0:16:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都在这些极易发生雪崩的山坡上冬眠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}within the snow on these avalanche-prone slopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.93,0:16:36.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,待春天来临  它们就出洞了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And when spring comes, they emerge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.07,0:16:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这些山脉中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}All across these mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.06,0:16:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,灰熊将巢筑在背风坡厚厚的积雪之下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}grizzly bears make their winter dens
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.75,0:16:59.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海拔高达三千米\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}10,000 feet up in the deep snow of leeward slopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.86,0:17:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们在隆冬半梦半醒之际\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And while they were half-asleep in the depths of winter,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.92,0:17:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,产下幼崽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}their young were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.16,0:17:13.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在这些熊宝宝正迈出他们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now these cubs are taking their first steps
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.82,0:17:15.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,走向外界的第一步\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}into the outside world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.43,0:17:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,熊妈妈带着三只幼崽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This mother is leading her three youngsters
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.39,0:17:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去找东西吃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to a place where they can find food.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.90,0:17:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们得尽快下山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They need to descend as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.98,0:18:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雪崩肆虐后的残骸清楚地表明\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The debris from an avalanche is clear evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.81,0:18:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这片山坡仍然非常不稳定\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that this slope is still dangerously unstable.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.91,0:18:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,此地不宜久留\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is not a place to dawdle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.04,0:18:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们继续前行还有另一个原因\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And they have another reason to keep moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.25,0:18:32.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在巢里呆了五个月后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}After five months in the den,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.12,0:18:35.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些灰熊饿得正慌\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}these bears are very hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.44,0:18:43.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这片山峰之间冬眠的灰熊\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Bears that have hibernated throughout these peaks
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.47,0:18:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在都下山了  那里的春天来得更早\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}now all descend to the valleys, where spring comes earliest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.65,0:19:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,落基山脉的季节变换迅速而突然\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the Rockies, seasonal change is swift and dramatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.97,0:19:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几天时间内\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In just a few days,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.35,0:19:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,白雪皑皑的山脉便会绿意盎然\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the slopes turn from white to green.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.08,0:19:44.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几周前还深埋在冰天雪地里的牧场\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Meadows that only a few weeks ago were buried beneath the snow
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.76,0:19:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在生机勃勃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are now full of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.98,0:20:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但山峦之间  好时光不会太久\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But in these mountains, the good times will not last long.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.14,0:20:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以灰熊必须尽快进食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So the bears must feed as fast as they can.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.18,0:20:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,夏季的几个月里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}During the summer months,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.71,0:20:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只成年灰熊靠吃植物能长一百八十公斤\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}an adult can put on 180 kilos gorging on plants
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.77,0:20:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要是能再...\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and, if they can catch them...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.71,0:20:31.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,逮几只土拨鼠就更好了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a marmot or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.31,0:20:39.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但现在灰熊们还有其他事情要做\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But just now, the bears have something else on their minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.61,0:20:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天气转暖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's becoming warmer,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.17,0:20:48.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,灰熊急切地想脱下它们厚重的冬衣\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the bears are keen to shed their thick winter coats.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.03,0:20:55.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,母熊给小熊们做了示范\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Mothers show the cubs what to do about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.13,0:21:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们很快就学会了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They'll soon catch on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.91,0:21:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一些树似乎特别适合搓背\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some trees, it seems, are particularly suitable for rubbing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.13,0:21:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,熊们都有自己的偏好\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Bears have their favourites
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.33,0:21:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们会长途跋涉  去找喜欢的树\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and will travel long distances to visit them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.27,0:21:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,身上有些痒  急需挠一挠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some itches just have to be scratched.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.35,0:21:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个山谷中大约有三十只熊\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are now around 30 bears in this one valley.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.08,0:22:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每只熊摩擦时都会留下易于辨认的独特气味\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As they rub, each leaves an individual and recognisable scent.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.31,0:22:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以树上很快会留有附近灰熊的气味\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So the tree soon carries a list of who's around,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.94,0:22:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或许可以避免个体之间的争斗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}which might help individuals to avoid a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.60,0:22:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了更好地散布自己的气味\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To best spread their scent,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.37,0:22:23.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们得用后背好好地蹭一蹭\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they really have to put their back into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.50,0:23:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是夏天很短暂\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But summer is short.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.96,0:23:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,痒痒挠满意之后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Itches satisfactorily scratched,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.70,0:23:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是时候该进食了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it's time to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.69,0:23:19.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几个月后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In a couple of months,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.98,0:23:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们就要回自己的窝里冬眠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they will have to return to their dens to hibernate,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.45,0:23:26.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以现在必须尽可能地增重\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so now they must put on as much weight as they can.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.06,0:23:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,山里的冬天来得迅猛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Winter in the mountains returns fast and hits hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.68,0:23:58.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,落基山脉地区的温度会降至零下五十四度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Temperatures in the Rockies will drop to -54 degrees,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.13,0:24:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以至于空气中的水分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so cold that moisture in the air
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.63,0:24:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会直接凝结成冰晶  俗称钻石尘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}freezes into tiny crystals called diamond dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.57,0:24:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,山猫是少数冬天还在活动的捕猎者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This bobcat is one of the few hunters to remain active in winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.20,0:24:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他领地内的大多数猎物都\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Most of his prey is now hidden beneath the snow
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.88,0:24:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,隐藏在茫茫大雪之下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that covers his entire territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.20,0:24:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他通过辨认极其微弱的声音来捕捉猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He hunts by listening for the faintest sound of movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.21,0:25:00.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了避免踩雪的脚步声暴露行踪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And to prevent crunching footsteps from revealing his presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.40,0:25:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他用岩石当落脚点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}he uses boulders as stepping stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.15,0:25:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,逮住一只老鼠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A mouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.85,0:25:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这远远不够\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But one is not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.53,0:25:49.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,积雪越深越难发现猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The deeper the snow, the harder it is to detect prey,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.10,0:25:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,努力捕食却往往空手而归\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the rewards for the effort can be disappointing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.51,0:25:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这么说毫不夸张\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To say the least.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.71,0:26:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,深冬时节积雪实在太深\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}By midwinter, the snow is so deep
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.17,0:26:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,山猫被迫离开他们的领地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that bobcats are forced to leave their territories
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.25,0:26:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,寻找更易于捕捉的猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to try and find easier hunting.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.83,0:26:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这只山猫运气不错\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And this bobcat may be in luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.21,0:26:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为这个山谷得自然之眷顾\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For this particular valley is blessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.80,0:26:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这条河永不结冰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A river here never freezes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.18,0:26:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,火山温泉带来的热量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's fed by a volcanic hot spring
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.50,0:27:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,使河水升温\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that heats these waters
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.35,0:27:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比周围空气的温度高了五十余度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to 50 degrees warmer than the surrounding air.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.38,0:27:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,各种饥肠辘辘的动物来此觅食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Hungry animals of all kinds come here to feed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.17,0:27:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到了冬天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Throughout the winter,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.33,0:27:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于那些老道的捕猎者而言\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the river is full of food
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.65,0:27:43.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,河里满是食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for those who know how to catch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.11,0:27:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这里连土狼都学会了捕鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here, even the coyotes have become fishermen.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.59,0:28:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是捕鱼对山猫来说很难\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But hunting is hard for a cat
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.77,0:28:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为他们讨厌下水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that's not used to getting its feet wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.66,0:28:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以他必须谨慎选择目标\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So he must choose his target with care.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.31,0:28:35.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,白颊鸭来了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Goldeneye ducks.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.29,0:28:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他能够靠近到扑得着吗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But can he get close enough to pounce?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.89,0:29:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许对岸的机会更大点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Perhaps he'll have more luck on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.19,0:29:36.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,河里的热气温暖了周围的树林\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here, steam from the river warms the surrounding trees,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.60,0:29:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以林子里可能有猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so up in the branches, there could be prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.64,0:29:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前提是他能爬得上去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If only he could get to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.76,0:29:52.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这有六米高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's 20 feet up.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.03,0:30:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最终收获一只松鼠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At last... a squirrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.29,0:30:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是很多  但是足以支撑他继续捕食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Not much, but enough to keep him going.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.68,0:30:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想要渡过山里的冬天需要坚韧不拔的意志\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To survive a winter in these mountains takes tenacity,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.00,0:30:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而山猫是其中的佼佼者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and bobcats have that in abundance.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.85,0:30:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是一座赤道雪山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Snow on the equator.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.24,0:30:53.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,与落基山脉不同  这里的山脉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Unlike the Rockies, in these mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.88,0:30:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有明显的四季\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}there are no marked seasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.00,0:31:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是非洲的肯尼亚山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is Africa's Mount Kenya.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.43,0:31:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海拔超过五千米\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's 17,000 feet high,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.72,0:31:18.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,峰顶温度比周围的热带草原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}which makes its summit some 30 degrees colder
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.90,0:31:20.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,低三十度左右\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}than the surrounding savanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.46,0:31:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,巨型石南  半边莲和千里光\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Giant heathers, lobelias and groundsel
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.39,0:31:31.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生长在山顶斜坡上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}grow on its upper slopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.87,0:31:34.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们在炎炎烈日下茁壮成长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They all thrive in the tropical sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.61,0:31:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,毕竟赤道每天都是夏天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}After all, every day is summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.99,0:31:43.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但一旦太阳下山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But once the sun sets,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.26,0:31:47.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每个夜晚都像冬天般寒冷\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}every night becomes as bitterly cold as winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.10,0:31:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,气温降到零下五度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The temperature drops to five degrees below freezing,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.63,0:32:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,山坡变成了冰雪花园\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}turning the mountainside into a garden of ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.58,0:32:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一切都冻结了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Everything freezes,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.62,0:32:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是木本千里光有办法保护自己\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the cabbage groundsels have a way of protecting themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.20,0:32:44.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们合起革质叶片形成一道保温层\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They close up their leathery leaves to form an insulating blanket
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.19,0:32:47.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以保护中心脆弱的蓓蕾\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that shields their vulnerable central bud.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.36,0:33:01.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,寒夜将尽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Night comes to an end...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.20,0:33:07.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阳光回归大地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}...and the sunshine returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.29,0:33:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,木本千里光舒展它们的叶子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The groundsels spread their leaves wide
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.27,0:33:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再一次沐浴在阳光之中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to bask in the sunshine once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.10,0:33:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安第斯山脉的黎明来到\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Dawn in the High Andes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.15,0:33:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这里  升起的朝阳同样解放了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here too, the rising sun brings rapid relief
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.08,0:33:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生活在火山山峰之间的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to animals living amongst these volcanic peaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.33,0:34:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,山兔鼠早早起来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Mountain viscacha are up early
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.00,0:34:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抢占最佳位置  享受第一缕阳光\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to claim the best places to catch the sun's first rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.52,0:34:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于其他的动物  太阳更加受到欢迎\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For others up here, the sunrise is even more welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.33,0:34:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里的海拔超过四千米\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At over 14,000 feet,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.70,0:34:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是世界上海拔最高的火烈鸟栖息地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}this is the highest flamingo colony in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.60,0:34:47.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里的夜晚非常寒冷\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At night, it gets so cold
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.95,0:34:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,连盐水湖都会结冰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that even this salty water freezes over.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.18,0:34:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些火烈鸟就被冻在了冰里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And now the flamingos are trapped in the ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.85,0:35:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,终于太阳晒薄了冰面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Eventually, the sun thins the ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.94,0:35:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是火烈鸟仍然需要努力冲破冰层\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but it's still a struggle for the flamingos to break free.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.06,0:35:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,走在薄冰上总是危机四伏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Walking on thin ice is always risky.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.74,0:35:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且当你踩着高跷的时候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And it's hard to retain one's dignity...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.92,0:35:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哪还顾得上体面和优雅\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}...especially when you're wearing stilts.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.11,0:36:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海拔如此之高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At these altitudes,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.10,0:36:13.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的热力很快从救星变成了威胁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the sun's power can quickly turn from salvation to threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.15,0:36:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由于大气稀薄\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The atmosphere is so thin,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.49,0:36:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无法阻挡紫外线的辐射\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}there is very little protection from ultraviolet radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.84,0:36:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上午十点钟在开阔地带逗留就已经十分危险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}By mid-morning, it's risky to linger out in the open.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.38,0:36:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鼠兔被迫寻找阴凉处避暑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The viscacha are forced to head for the shade.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.68,0:36:47.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而湖面上则无处可藏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Out on the lake, there is nowhere to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.64,0:36:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,盐湖的白色盐层反射着\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The white crust of the soda lake
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.76,0:36:57.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的光芒\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}reflects the sun's glare
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.10,0:37:01.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,增强了紫外线的杀伤力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and increases the impact of its ultraviolet rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.89,0:37:07.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正午时分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}By midday,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.71,0:37:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,裸露的人类肌肤四分钟内就会被晒伤\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}uncovered human skin will burn in four minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.54,0:37:20.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这似乎无法妨碍到火烈鸟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But this doesn't seem to bother the flamingos.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.46,0:37:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事实上  它们正在列队游行\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In fact, they are on parade.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.27,0:37:56.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在繁殖季节\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}During the breeding season,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.94,0:38:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即便在一天中最热的时刻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the flamingos perform these peculiar courtship dances
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.70,0:38:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,火烈鸟也在不停表演着奇异的求爱舞蹈\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}even through the hottest time of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.35,0:38:14.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们求爱心切  甚至没时间停下来进食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They are so eager, they don't even pause to feed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.24,0:38:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽管求爱规则让人摸不着头脑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The rules are something of a mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.15,0:38:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但在跳了一个月之后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but, after a month of dancing,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.81,0:38:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有的鸟儿都配对成功\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}all the birds will have paired off
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.74,0:38:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并准备开始交配\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and will be getting ready to mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.18,0:38:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,高山之上  很少有其他动物来打扰火烈鸟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Up here, there are few other creatures to bother the flamingos,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.80,0:38:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从另一方面讲  也少有其他动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but then, few other creatures
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.61,0:38:58.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能够忍受这样的生活条件\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}could even tolerate these conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.82,0:39:04.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于耐力极佳的动物而言\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So for animals that have the endurance,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.31,0:39:08.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,深山堪称生存的圣殿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}mountains can be sanctuaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.94,0:39:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些在我们看来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But rocky peaks which to us, perhaps,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.28,0:39:26.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,似乎象征着永恒的岩石山峰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}seem a symbol of permanence,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.96,0:39:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实要脆弱得多\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are more fragile than they appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.84,0:39:35.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如今在阿尔卑斯山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Today in the Alps,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.89,0:39:40.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人类的侵犯甚至影响到顶峰的环境状况\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}human encroachment is changing even the highest summits.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.46,0:39:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在落基山脉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the Rockies,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.59,0:39:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,升高的气温缩短了冬眠的时间\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}rising temperatures are shortening winter hibernation
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.29,0:40:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也阻碍了食料植物的生长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and stifling the growth of valuable food plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.84,0:40:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在安第斯山脉  一些冰川\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And in the Andes, some glaciers
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.74,0:40:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在短短三十年内面积减少了百分之五十\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}have shrunk by 50% in just 30 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.34,0:40:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如今  甚至连喜马拉雅山脉都变得十分脆弱\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Even the Himalayas are now vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.20,0:40:35.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里汇集着大多数世上最高的山峰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With most of the world's tallest peaks
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.56,0:40:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,占地面积八十六万平方公里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and covering a third of a million square miles,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.58,0:40:41.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是世界上最大的山脉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}this is the greatest mountain range of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.80,0:40:51.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而这里气温升高的速度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And here, temperatures are now rising
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.17,0:40:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快于全球平均水平\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}faster than the global average.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.83,0:40:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雪线向山峰处退去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the snow line retreats further and further up these peaks,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.73,0:41:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,野生动植物的生存空间日益减少\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}there is less and less space for wildlife,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.42,0:41:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恶化的条件威胁着\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and that is a challenge
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.28,0:41:09.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一种美丽山地动物的生存\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for one of the most majestic of all mountain creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.84,0:41:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雪豹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The snow leopard.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.57,0:41:39.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由于行踪隐蔽  雪豹的生活细节一直是个谜\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Seldom seen, the detail of their lives has long been a mystery,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.56,0:41:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但现在  借助最先进的远程摄像技术\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but now, at last, helped by the latest remote-camera technology,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.90,0:41:49.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们终于能够近距离观察他们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}we are getting closer to them than ever before.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.49,0:41:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雪豹数量稀少\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They are very rare,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.79,0:41:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,百平方公里内只有四只\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}only about four of them in 40 square miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.88,0:42:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是因为猎物数量不足以维系更多的生命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There is simply not enough prey to sustain more.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.12,0:42:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雪豹是独居动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They live solitary lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.91,0:42:15.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽管如此  他们仍能很好地掌握\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Nonetheless, they are well aware of the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.62,0:42:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,邻居们的存在和动向\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the movements of their neighbours,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.02,0:42:22.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为他们会在几个特殊地点给对方留下信息\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}because they leave messages in a few special places.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.11,0:42:28.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,像这样用脸颊摩擦特定的岩石\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They rub particular rocks with their cheeks
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.80,0:42:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再喷射上自己的尿液\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and then spray them with urine.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.25,0:42:41.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两种味道创造出了独一无二的签名\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The two perfumes create a unique signature.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.14,0:42:47.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽管没有直接看到彼此\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Any other leopard can know
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.04,0:42:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雪豹也能判断出\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}which of its neighbours passed this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.15,0:42:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是哪位邻居曾经到此一游\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}without ever making direct contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.91,0:43:00.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有些时候雪豹们必须聚到一起\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But there are times when snow leopards must come together,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.25,0:43:04.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而场面通常都很暴力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the event is often violent.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.04,0:43:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只成年雌雪豹和她的女儿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}An adult female and her daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.32,0:43:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雌雪豹花费了两年时间哺育幼崽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She has devoted the last two years to raising her cub
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.89,0:43:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很快  幼崽就要断奶了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and very soon, it will be weaned.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.47,0:43:44.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,目前  幼崽依旧完全依靠自己的母亲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For now, the cub is still entirely dependent on its mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.69,0:43:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这样长时间的共处会引发问题\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But staying together as long as this could cause problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.35,0:44:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雌雪豹此时又到了发情期\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The female is now in heat again,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.48,0:44:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雄雪豹只需闻到她的信号便会知晓\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and any male that smells her signature will know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.11,0:44:20.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从此刻起  雌雪豹幼崽的生命陷入了危机\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}From this moment on, her cub's life is at risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.94,0:44:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雄雪豹会杀死非亲生的幼崽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Males kill cubs that are not their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.46,0:44:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但雌雪豹此时正被体内无法控制的欲望驱使着\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the mother is now driven by an urge that she cannot control.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.87,0:44:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她让雄雪豹知道了她的确切位置\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She lets the males know exactly where she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.11,0:45:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从这片高地  她的声音可以传遍方圆数公里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}From up here, she can be heard for miles around.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.64,0:45:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只年轻雄雪豹在荒野中出现\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A young male emerges from the wilderness,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.33,0:45:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,迫切地想要找到雌雪豹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}eager to find her.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.64,0:45:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雪豹们很少碰面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Snow leopards meet so infrequently
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.70,0:45:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以致整个场面充斥着不确定和紧张的气氛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that there is uncertainty and tension.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.34,0:45:45.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而更糟的还在后面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And it's about to get worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.10,0:45:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,另一只体型更为健壮的雄雪豹也来了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Another, bigger male has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.43,0:46:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雌雪豹和幼崽被困在两个竞争对手之间\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The mother and cub are trapped between the rivals.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.57,0:46:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幼崽命在旦夕\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The cub is now in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.25,0:46:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,母亲必须尽快行动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Mother must act fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.73,0:46:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了转移雄雪豹对幼崽的注意力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To divert the males' attention from her cub,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.49,0:46:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她顺从地滚动着身体\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}she rolls over submissively.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.44,0:46:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雄雪豹的注意力都集中在了雌雪豹身上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With the males fixed on the female,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.51,0:46:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幼崽得以借此机会脱身\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the cub has a chance to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.81,0:46:53.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两只雄雪豹从两侧接近雌雪豹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The males close in on the mother from both sides,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.98,0:46:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,渴望将其占为己有\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}keen to claim her for their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.96,0:47:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,决斗在所难免\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A fight is inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.99,0:47:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雌雪豹试图逃跑并保护她的幼崽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The female moves to escape and protect her cub.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.39,0:47:31.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但健硕的雄雪豹紧跟着她\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the big male follows her.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.43,0:47:47.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在没有交配前  雄雪豹是不会放她走的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He will not let her leave until he has mated with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.32,0:48:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雄雪豹走后  雌雪豹终于与幼崽重聚\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With the males gone, the female is at last reunited with her cub.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.31,0:48:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但她不幸受了伤\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But she has been injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.06,0:48:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多亏了她的妈妈  幼崽才能活下来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The cub, however, is alive, thanks to its mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.24,0:48:45.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在雌雪豹伤口痊愈之前  她已无法捕猎\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Until her injury heals, she won't be able to hunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.38,0:48:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,山地动物就这样挣扎在存活的边缘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Mountain animals survive on the very edge of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.66,0:48:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雌雪豹和幼崽从此消失不见\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Mother and cub were not seen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.71,0:49:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到一个月后  在高高的山脊上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Until over a month later, high on a ridge,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.72,0:49:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,远程摄像机捕捉到了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a remote camera was triggered.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.15,0:49:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雌雪豹的身影\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The female cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.03,0:49:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她已不再跛足而行  却形单影只\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She's no longer limping, but she's now alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.53,0:49:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雌雪豹离开后一个小时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Then, an hour after the female has left,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.05,0:49:35.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,摄像机再次启动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the camera is triggered again.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.74,0:49:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是幼崽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's her cub,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.78,0:49:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开始了迈向成年和独立的第一步\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}taking her first steps towards adulthood and independence.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.34,0:49:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幼崽大概很少有机会与母亲重逢了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She is unlikely to see her mother again.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.88,0:49:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但不时地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But every now and then,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.68,0:49:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们会通过在岩石上留下的信息\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they will be reunited through the messages they leave
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.74,0:50:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,间接地团聚\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}on the marking rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.88,0:50:08.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幼崽虽被母亲成功养大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Her mother has succeeded in raising her,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.59,0:50:11.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但前方的生存之路仍充满荆棘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but life ahead will be challenging,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.90,0:50:15.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而她几乎全部要独自面对\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and she will spend nearly all of it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.08,0:50:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有最顽强的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Only the toughest can survive
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.99,0:50:22.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,才能在世界最高屋脊上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}among the savage beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.82,0:50:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这片美丽的蛮夷之地存活\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}of the world's highest mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.60,0:50:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下一集\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Next time...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.18,0:50:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们到世界各地探索丛林\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}we explore the world's jungles.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.59,0:50:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球上充满惊喜和创造力无与伦比的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Places of surprise and invention unrivalled on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.66,0:50:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那里的生存之战最为激烈\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}...where the battle for survival is at its most intense.

